Cheat file ardrone custom code

1.follow steps for compiler setup:
http://taghof.github.io/Navigation-for-Robots-with-WIFI-and-CV/blog/2012/01/13/Compiling-Code-For-The-ARDrone/
codesourcery-arm-2009q3.sh

sudo apt-get install ia32-libs
if using a 64 bit system

2.upload code to drone
$ ftp 192.168.1.1
Connected to 192.168.1.1.
ftp> put hello_arm 

# cd data/video/
# chmod +x hello_arm 
# ./hello_arm 

3. Control motors directly with pwm
http://wiki.paparazziuav.org/wiki/AR_Drone_2/Motor_driver
http://blog.perquin.com/blog/ardrone-motor-controller/

works perfect just change motor port from /dev/ttyPA1 to /dev/ttyO0

./sbin/restart: to restart

ps to show which program run
kill .. any program (ex: kill 810 for main program)

4. udp control of the motors using remote machine
perquin`s udp client and server works well--tested


5. Aquire imu data to udp
testing perquins code - no good protocol is different
paparazzi has a ardrone 2 code - writing main file for testing
navdata2 folder works
build using: arm-none-linux-gnueabi-g++ -lpthread -o navdata_test gpio_ardrone.c navdata_test.c-ok


6. Implement and tune an AHRS


7. implement a simple attitude controller with ground keyboard control



